Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel). Pop onto a large
#baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then
sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g}.

Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf of your oven until golden,
~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

== Crispy Japanese Fried Chicken ==

Crack the @egg{1} into a #bowl{} and whisk with the @soy sauce{12.5%ml}.

Cut each @British chicken thighs{4} into 3-4 pieces.

Put the @panko breadcrumbs{75%g} into another bowl and season with
@salt{1/4%tsp} and @pepper{}.

Season the chicken, then dip into the egg and then the breadcrumbs, ensuring
it's completely coated. Transfer to a clean #plate{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging and discard any excess egg.

Pop a large #frying pan{} on high heat and add enough @oil{} to completely coat
the bottom of the pan.

> TIP: You want the oil to be hot so the chicken fries properly - heat for
> 2-3 mins before you add the chicken.

Once the oil is hot, carefully lay the chicken in the pan and fry until golden,
~{4-5%minutes}. Turn every 1-2 mins and adjust the heat if needed.

Transfer to another baking tray (keep the pan) and bake on the middle shelf
until cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

== Sriracha Mayo ==

While the chicken bakes, mix together the @mayonnaise{64%g} and
@sriracha sauce{15%g} in a #small bowl{} (keep some mayo aside if anyone doesn't
want spicy mayo). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then set aside.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}).

== Stir-Fried Vegetables ==

Discard the oil from the chicken pan and wipe it clean. Pop back on
medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{}.

Once hot, add the @sliced mushrooms{80%g} and @Tenderstem broccoli{150%g}.
Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and stir-fry until starting to brown,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute} more, then add a splash of @water{}
and cover with a #lid{} (or some #foil{}).

Cook until the broccoli is tender, ~{3-4%minutes}.

== To Serve ==

When ready, share the fried chicken, sesame wedges and stir-fried vegetables
between your plates.

Serve with the sriracha mayo for dipping.

Enjoy!